The paper deals with information theory, specifically lossless source coding and guessing moments, which are related to the Arimoto-R\'{e}nyi conditional entropy. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses bounds on the reliability function of discrete memoryless sources, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from probability theory and statistics, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
